    <!-- http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/Granulometry -->


    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/Granulometry">
        <rdfs:comment>CQ: Crushing and Milling
What is the particle size and size distribution of the mining waste?</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:comment>MINNERSA, SGS
In this case, it is the classification of a mineral&apos;s size. A particle size analysis determines the proportion of minerals in different fractions. This is an important characteristic when processing minerals.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/GreenHouseGasEmission -->


    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/GreenHouseGasEmission">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/EnvironmentalImpact"/>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/GrindingOperation -->


    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/GrindingOperation">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/MineralProcessingOperation"/>
        <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">METSO Handbook : Grinding is the stage of size reduction (wet or dry) where the liberation size for individual minerals can be reached. By further size reduction filler (mineral powder) is produced.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">MWEI BREF : Comminution process yielding a fine product (&lt; 1 mm), where size reduction 
is accomplished by abrasion and impact and sometimes supported by the free 
motion of unconnected media such as rods, balls and pebbles.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/GroundPenetratingRadarOperation -->


