    <!-- http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/Measurement -->


    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/Measurement"/>
    


    <!-- http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/Metal -->


    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/Metal">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/Mineral"/>
        <rdfs:comment>More concept will be cleared in EXPERT
Currently, we read from the internet, &quot;Metal that exist in nature are minerals&quot;

https://www.geologyin.com/2016/03/what-is-difference-between-rock-mineral.html</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:comment>On the basis of current infomation, received from the partner for queastion 3
3) What form those metals are present in those minerals, 

These things will be defined clearly with expert discussion.</rdfs:comment>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/Methodology -->


    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://www.semanticweb.org/rajesh.piryani/ontologies/2025/3/SCIMIN_CRM/Methodology"/>
    


